-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.153","title":"[audit][service] Keep Weighted load balancer state synchronized with dynamic topology updates","description":"src/service/load_balance.rs now supports dynamic backend insert/remove via push(), remove(), and update_from_discover(), but the Weighted strategy keeps a fixed weight/state vector that is never updated when topology changes. That can make newly inserted backends unreachable, misalign removal indices, and skew SWRR selection after discovery updates. Rework Weighted so its internal state stays synchronized with backend topology changes, add focused regressions for discovery insert/remove and direct push/remove paths, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","notes":"Fixed weighted load-balancer topology/state mismatch in src/service/load_balance.rs. Weighted now synchronizes its weights/current_weights with push(), remove(), and update_from_discover() via strategy topology hooks, preserving backend/weight alignment under dynamic discovery changes. Added focused regressions: lb_weighted_discovery_insert_syncs_strategy_state, lb_weighted_push_syncs_strategy_state, lb_weighted_remove_reindexes_strategy_weights. Validation: rch cargo fmt --check PASS; rch cargo check --all-targets PASS; rch isolated cargo test -p asupersync --lib lb_weighted_ -- --nocapture --test-threads=1 PASS (3/3). Post-close correction: removed an accidental drop(backends) in push() so backend insertion and strategy-state sync remain atomic under the backend lock. Clippy remains blocked by existing unrelated warnings/errors outside this bead (spawn_blocking.rs, timeout.rs, net/dns/resolver.rs).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SapphireCliff","created_at":"2026-03-11T10:32:06.890761805Z","created_by":"SapphireCliff","updated_at":"2026-03-11T10:53:30.229960749Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T10:49:35.029213224Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.153","depends